2008-01-01 [LOC Iran] ( [ORG IR] ) Narcotics ; crime A newspaper report on January 1 , 2008 that [LOC Iran] hanged two convicted drug traffickers in the southeastern city of [LOC Zahedan] . This brings the number of executions for 2007 to at least 297 . A newspaper report on January 1 , 2008 that [LOC Iran] hanged two convicted drug traffickers in the southeastern city of [LOC Zahedan] . This brings the number of executions for 2007 to at least 297 . The hardline [ORG Kayhan] newspaper said the men were identified as [PER Mehdi Rigi Javan] and [PER Naser] hedieh sasooli and were hanged in prison on December 31 , 2007 for trafficking 59 kilos ( 130 pounds ) of heroin . An AFP count compiled from local press reports stated that the executions brought the number of people hanged in [LOC Iran] in 2007 to at least 297 . This figure well exceeds the 177 convicted criminals executed in 2006 According to [ORG Amnesty International] . [LOC Iran] is currently the leader in death penalty executions after [LOC China] . The number of executions increased in [LOC Iran] last year amid a campaign that is aimed at improving security in society . The campaign has been aimed at arresting drug-traffickers , rapists and those deemed a social menace . Dozens of such criminals have been hanged in public . Several executions have occurred in major cities . Capital offences in [LOC Iran] include murder , rape , armed robbery , serious drug trafficking and adultery . Rights groups have accused [LOC Iran] of employing the death penalty excessively . Authorities say capital punishment is an effective deterrent that is only used after an exhaustive judicial process . 2008-01-02 [LOC Iran] ( [ORG IR] ) Narcotics ; crime Government of [LOC Iran] hangs 5 drug traffickers in growing number of executions . The marked increase in executions in [LOC Iran] since 2006 is defended by the Government as a means of increasing security and criticized by human rights groups as excessive . The Government of [LOC Iran] hanged 5 convicted drug traffickers on 02 January 2008 . The 5 hangings were the most recent in an increasing number of executions in [LOC Iran] . [LOC Iran] is an [MISC Islamic] republic . [MISC Iranian] state media reported -- 3 of the 5 drug traffickers were hanged in a public square in the central city of [LOC Qom] . 2 of the 5 drug traffickers were hanged in the eastern city of [LOC Zahedan] . The hangings were the first [MISC Iranian] executions to be reported in 2008 . The official [ORG IRNA] news agency stated that the 3 drug traffickers hanged in [LOC Qom] were -- [PER Safarali] [PER Nazari Ashkar] convicted of trafficking 455 grams ( 1 pound ) of heroin . [PER Sohbatollah Malaki] who trafficked 170 grams ( 0.3 pounds ) of heroin . [PER Habib oliaei] convicted of smuggling 590 grams ( 1.3 pounds ) . Local judiciary official [PER Hoda torshizi] stated that by implementing [PER God] 's law the [MISC Iranian] government is increasing security in society and sending a message that violating the law will not be tolerated in [LOC Qom] . State media did not identify the 2 convicts hanged in [LOC Zahedan] but stated that they had been found guilty of transporting 5.25 kilograms ( 11.5 pounds ) of heroin . [MISC Iranian] law administers severe penalties for drug trafficking . A person found guilty of smuggling more than 30 grams ( 0.06 pounds ) of heroin or 5 kilograms ( 11 pounds ) of opium may receive the death penalty . According to an AFP figure compiled from press reports the government of [LOC Iran] executed at least 297 people in 2007 . The total was a marked increase from 2006 in which 177 people were executed according to [ORG Amnesty International] . The number of executions increased dramatically in 2007 amid a campaign which [MISC Iranian] authorities state is aimed at improving security in society . [LOC Iran] currently administers the death penalty more than any other country besides [LOC China] . Capital offenses in [LOC Iran] include murder , rape , armed robbery , serious drug trafficking and adultery . Human rights groups have accused [LOC Iran] of excessive resort to the death penalty but [MISC Iranian] authorities state that capital punishment is an effective deterrent that is used only after an exhaustive judicial process . 2008-01-07 [LOC China] ( [ORG CN] ) ; [ORG Democratic People 's Republic of Korea] ( [ORG KP] ) proliferation ; international ; military [LOC US] experts report [MISC Chinese] plans to dispatch troops to [LOC North Korea] and secure [LOC North Korea] 's nuclear arsenal in the event of instability . A report compiled by experts from the Center for [LOC Strategic] and [ORG International Studies] , the [ORG US Institute of Peace] and the [ORG Asia Foundation] stated that [LOC China] has contingency plans to dispatch [PER Chinese People] 's [ORG Liberation Army] ( [ORG PLA] ) troops to [LOC North Korea] and secure nuclear weapons in the event of instability in [LOC North Korea] . The experts visited [LOC China] 20070600 to confer with [MISC Chinese] military researchers . The report stated -- [LOC China] 's strong preference is to receive formal authorization and coordinate closely with the [ORG UN] in any possible intervention . [LOC China] would take unilateral action to restore stability if the international community did not react in a timely manner as the internal order in [LOC North Korea] deteriorated rapidly . The report stated -- [ORG PLA] researchers claim that contingency plans exist for the [ORG PLA] to perform three possible missions in [LOC North Korea] -- humanitarian , peacekeeping and environmental control . The environmental control measures are intended to clean up nuclear contamination resulting from a strike on [MISC North Korean] nuclear facilities near the [MISC Sino-North] [MISC Korean] border and to secure nuclear weapons and fissile materials . The report stated -- [LOC China] 's main priority in the event of instability in [LOC North Korea] would be preve