] freighter carrying a large cargo of arms stated that the pirates may soon be collecting their ransom . After difficult negotiations likened by several people involved to bazaar-style haggling the parties are close to reaching a deal in which the pirates would be paid millions of dollars and the ship freed . A businessman in xarardheere , [LOC Somalia] named [PER Ahmed Omar] stated that the pirates and the ship owners have agreed on a ransom of approximately 8 million [LOC U.S.] dollars and the ship may be freed on 08 October 2008 or 09 October 2008 . Xarardheere is a notorious pirate base on the coast of [LOC Somalia] . Maritime officials in [LOC Kenya] stated that critical details have yet to be agreed upon . One such detail involves the pirates' request for a guarantee that they would not be arrested or attacked by the armada of [MISC American] warships currently encircling them . A [MISC Kenyan] maritime official stated anonymously that such negotiations are complex and involve more than the financial aspect . On 08 October 2008 the official stated that progress is being made and the parties are approaching an agreement . The pirates initially requested 35 million [LOC U.S.] dollars and then reduced their request to 20 million [LOC U.S.] dollars . The pirates have consistently expressed willingness to negotiate the financial figures . More than 25 ships have been hijacked in 2008 off the [LOC Somalia] coast with a typical ransom of between 1 and 2 million [LOC U.S.] dollars . The pirates aboard the [MISC Ukrainian] ship have stated that upon receipt of payment in [MISC American] dollars and preferably in 100 dollar bills the ship , its cargo and the 20 sailors on board will be released . The original country of destination for the arms shipment aboard the [MISC Ukrainian] ship is being questioned . Shortly after the freighter was hijacked on 25 September 2008 the [MISC Kenyan] government claimed that the weapons on board were being shipped for [LOC Kenya] 's mi