Costa] said that [LOC Afghanistan] has produced so much opium in recent years that the [ORG Taliban] are cutting back poppy cultivation and stockpiling raw opium in an effort to support prices and preserve a major source of financing for the insurgency . Head of the [ORG U.N.] drug office [PER Antonio Maria Costa] said that [LOC Afghanistan] has produced so much opium in recent years that the [ORG Taliban] are cutting back poppy cultivation and stockpiling raw opium in an effort to support prices and preserve a major source of financing for the insurgency . [PER Costa] said this to reporters last week as the [ORG U.N. Drug Office Office] prepared to release its latest survey of [LOC Afghanistan] 's opium crop . The survey showed that poppy cultivation had retreated in much of [LOC Afghanistan] and was overwhelmingly concentrated in 7 of 34 provinces where the insurgency remains strong , most of those in the south . The survey was issued November 27 , 2008 . The [ORG United Nations] found that the result was a 19 percent reduction in the amount of land devoted to opium in [LOC Afghanistan] even though the total tonnage of opium produced dropped by just 6 percent . The study stated that the high output per acre was attributed to a good growing season in the south . The southern region is a heavily irrigated area where the [ORG Taliban] maintained a strong presence in 5 provinces and have systematically encouraged opium cultivation as a way to finance their insurgency for several years . The [ORG U.N.] estimates the insurgents made as much as 300 million dollars from the opium trade last year . [PER Costa] said a lot of war effort can be funded with 2 to 300 million dollars . The [ORG Taliban] have producing an amount of opium that far exceeds world demand due to 3 successive years of bumper crops . [PER Costa] said the result was a glut that was depressing the price , which dropped by approximately 20 percent . [PER Costa] said that the fact that prices had not collapsed already was evidence that the [ORG Taliban] , drug lords and even some farmers have stockpiled the opium . An increasing amount is also being processed in [LOC Afghanistan] . [PER Costa] added that insurgents have been holding significant amounts of opium . [PER Costa] said the surplus is as much as 11000 tons , or more than twice world demand in the last 3 years and threatened to devalue their stockpiles . The [ORG United Nations] found that [LOC Afghanistan] produced 8500 tons of opium in 2008 . World demand was estimated at about 4400 tons per year . The [ORG Taliban] this year are taking a passive stance toward cultivation and putting less pressure on [MISC Afghan] farmers to plant opium poppy . This then supports the current price . [PER Costa] is an [MISC Italian] diplomat who has served at the [ORG U.N. Office] on Drugs and Crime for 6 years . 
